modules.description: Provides functions to manage session keys with expiration, including generating unique keys with optional expiry, retrieving session values with their expiry periods, and clearing stored sessions. Operates on session keys as strings, values as strings, and expiry periods as 64-bit integers. Used to handle temporary user sessions in web applications, ensuring data is removed after a specified time.

Handles cookie-based session management and persistence, including creation, retrieval, and expiration of session data. Works with HTTP request and response objects, session identifiers, and backend storage systems like in-memory or file-based stores. Used to implement authenticated routes in web servers, such as enforcing access control based on session validity.

Manages session state for Webmachine resources by providing methods to retrieve, update, and persist session data. It operates on session identifiers and associated key-value pairs stored in a structured format. Used to track user-specific data across HTTP requests in a web application.
